for_each_prime_number - iterate over each prime upto a value @prime: the current prime number in this iteration @max: the upper limit Starting from the first prime number 2 iterate over each prime number up to the @max value. On each iteration, @prime is set to the current prime number. @max should be less than ULONG_MAX to ensure termination. To begin with @prime set to 1 on the first iteration use for_each_prime_number_from() instead
